---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Charter for Sovereign Public Information | OpenPublicInfo.ie">
  <main class="py-20">
    <article class="container-tight prose prose-slate max-w-none">
      <header class="mb-16 border-b-4 border-brand-text pb-8">
        <span class="text-brand-accent font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-sm mb-4 block">Foundational Principles</span>
        <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-black uppercase leading-none mb-6">
          Charter for Sovereign<br/> Public Information
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-slate-500 font-medium">
          A framework for accessible, platform-neutral, and resilient public communication in Ireland.
        </p>
      </header>

      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black uppercase mb-6">The Mandate</h2>
        <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Publicly funded information is a public good. Access to vital updates regarding transport, safety, health, and utilities must never be contingent on membership in a private social network or the acceptance of third-party tracking.
        </p>
        <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed">
          This charter outlines the three core principles that should govern all state-funded digital communication.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- The Three Pillars -->
      <section class="space-y-16 mb-24">
        <div class="border-l-8 border-brand-accent pl-8">
          <h3 class="text-4xl font-black uppercase mb-4 text-brand-text">1. Source-First Publication</h3>
          <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-700">
            The official state-owned website or application must be the <strong>Single Source of Truth (SSOT)</strong>. All real-time updates and service alerts must be published to the official domain <em>prior to</em> or <em>simultaneous with</em> distribution on any third-party social media platform.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-8 border-brand-accent pl-8">
          <h3 class="text-4xl font-black uppercase mb-4 text-brand-text">2. Platform Neutrality</h3>
          <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-700">
            Vital public information must be accessible to all citizens without the requirement for a private account, a login, or a specific third-party application. Public bodies must maintain <strong>digital sovereignty</strong>, ensuring their primary communication channel remains operational and accessible independent of private corporate infrastructure.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-8 border-brand-accent pl-8">
          <h3 class="text-4xl font-black uppercase mb-4 text-brand-text">3. Open Data Standards</h3>
          <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-700">
            Public alerts must be distributed using open, machine-readable formats (such as RSS, JSON, or industry-standard transit feeds). This ensures that information can be freely and safely aggregated by community groups, local media, and independent developers, fostering a resilient and distributed information ecosystem.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-16 bg-slate-900 text-white p-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black uppercase mb-6 text-brand-accent">Why This Matters</h2>
        <div class="space-y-6 opacity-90 text-lg">
          <p>
            <strong>Accessibility:</strong> Ensuring that the elderly, the privacy-conscious, and those with disabilities are not digitally excluded from public life.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>Accountability:</strong> Official domains provide a permanent, state-controlled record of public announcements, unlike social media feeds subject to deletion or algorithmic suppression.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>Efficiency:</strong> Modernizing the public sector workflow from manual, social-media-first posting to an automated, source-driven distribution model.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <footer class="mt-24 pt-12 border-t border-slate-200 text-slate-500 italic text-sm text-center">
        <p>This charter is maintained by the OpenPublicInfo.ie initiative. For inquiries, contact <a href="mailto:munim2020@gmail.com" class="text-brand-accent underline">Munim Kazia</a>.</p>
        <div class="mt-8">
          <a href="/" class="text-brand-text font-black uppercase tracking-widest no-underline border-b-2 border-brand-accent pb-1 hover:text-brand-accent transition-colors">Return to Main Page</a>
        </div>
      </footer>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>
